- Have you eaten anything?
- No.

03:36.717 --> 03:40.888
Hey, look, what is this, a picnic?
Come on. Let's go, man.
We got ten minutes to go.

03:48.562 --> 03:51.732
- Punch me out, man.
- You got it.

04:31.104 --> 04:35.526
Any word from the LAPD intelligence,
if there is such a thing?

04:35.692 --> 04:38.111
- Not yet, sir.
- Of course not.

04:38.237 --> 04:42.115
Because we're a covert
anti-terrorism team that is so secret...

04:42.199 --> 04:44.201
that when we snap our fingers
nothin' happens!

04:55.838 --> 04:58.048
Sheriff's department?
Airport police?

04:58.215 --> 05:00.968
Still waiting. But Interpol
insists he's in Tripoli.

05:01.176 --> 05:04.638
Yeah, well, you-you trust... You trust
that billion-dollar satellite, okay?

05:04.721 --> 05:07.808
I'll trust a ten-dollar snitch
at this point.

05:09.226 --> 05:12.187
- Sean, look...
- What?

05:12.312 --> 05:15.065
Why don't you just give 'em
a little break, okay?

05:15.232 --> 05:18.902
We'll take a break
when the case breaks, okay?

05:24.908 --> 05:26.827
Hallelujah

05:26.910 --> 05:30.998
Hallelujah, hallelujah
Hallelujah

05:31.165 --> 05:33.041
Hallelujah

05:33.167 --> 05:35.752
Hallelujah, hallelujah

05:35.919 --> 05:41.008
For the Lord God
Omnipotent reigneth

05:41.175 --> 05:42.926
Hallelu... Hallelu...
Hallelujah

05:43.093 --> 05:47.097
For the Lord God
Omnipotent reigneth

05:47.264 --> 05:50.934
Hallelu... Hallelu...
Hallelu... Hallelu... Hallelujah

05:51.101 --> 05:57.024
For the Lord God
Omnipotent reigneth

05:57.191 --> 06:00.861
Hallelujah

06:00.944 --> 06:05.365
- And he shall reign for ever and ever
- I never really enjoyed The Messiah.

06:05.532 --> 06:08.619
- In fact, I think it's fucking boring.
- And he shall reign for ever and ever

06:08.785 --> 06:13.790
But your voice makes even a hack
like Handel seem like a genius.

06:14.958 --> 06:18.629
Hallelujah, hallelujah

06:18.795 --> 06:20.881
Hallelujah, hallelujah

06:20.964 --> 06:23.133
Hallelujah

06:23.300 --> 06:25.469
Hallelujah, hallelujah

06:25.636 --> 06:32.976
Hallelujah

06:33.810 --> 06:36.063
Victor... When we...
When we put this thing to bed,

06:36.230 --> 06:38.649
y-you can brand
the Fourth Amendment on my butt.

06:38.815 --> 06:42.319
- Thank you.
- Sir, excuse me.
Your wife is on line one.

06:42.486 --> 06:46.073
Sean! A jet was just chartered.
Anderson Airfield.

06:46.240 --> 06:48.825
Guess who paid the bill in cash?
Pollux Troy.

06:48.992 --> 06:51.828
- Put one of our people on that plane.
- Wait! We still got no sign of Castor!

06:51.995 --> 06:55.916
Pollux doesn't fly without
Big Brother. Now come on!

07:36.123 --> 07:40.544
You're 26 minutes late.
The casing didn't fit, right?

07:40.711 --> 07:43.547
Yeah, I told you goddam Dietrich
would try to pawn off some...

07:43.714 --> 07:45.716
cheap-shit North Korean plastic.

07:45.883 --> 07:48.886
Casing fit like a condom.

07:49.052 --> 07:52.389
You didn't deviate
from the plan, did you, Pollux?

07:52.556 --> 07:55.225
Well, how long did you want me
to sit here twiddling my thumbs?

07:55.392 --> 07:59.062
I paid for the jet.
Save us some time.

07:59.229 --> 08:03.650
That's what the boys are for,
to hide our famous faces.

08:12.993 --> 08:15.662
If I didn't love you so damn
much, I'd have to kill you, bro.

08:15.829 --> 08:18.499
I hate it when you
call me bro.

08:27.508 --> 08:29.510
You guys are paid
to protect him from everybody,

08:29.676 --> 08:31.929
including himself.

08:32.095 --> 08:36.600
And stay away from downtown on the 18th.
It's gonna be a little, um, smoggy.

08:40.020 --> 08:41.855
Okay, my passengers are here.
I gotta go.

08:47.277 --> 08:49.947
Let's go. Let's go.
I'm bored. Let's go.

08:50.113 --> 08:52.783
- Here you go.
- Bravo.

08:52.950 --> 08:55.702
Would you like anything else
once we're airborne?

08:55.869 --> 08:57.955
Oh, a peach.

08:59.873 --> 09:02.793
Sit. Come here.

09:07.297 --> 09:10.884
You know, I can, uh,
eat a peach for hours.

09:13.804 --> 09:16.223
Um, come here.

09:16.390 --> 09:20.978
If I were to send you flowers,
where would I, uh...

09:21.144 --> 09:23.564
No, wait. Let me rephrase.

09:23.730 --> 09:28.068
If I were to let you
suck my tongue,

09:29.403 --> 09:32.239
would you be grateful?

09:53.760 --> 09:55.929
There's someone on the runway.

09:59.349 --> 10:02.102
Get off of me!

10:15.532 --> 10:18.535
- Archer.
- FBI!

10:24.833 --> 10:28.212
This is a very big gun.
Fly the fuckin' plane!

10:32.341 --> 10:34.551
Come on. That's it.

10:38.555 --> 10:42.184
- Come on. Let's go!
- Goddam it. Don't play chicken
with a goddam jet!

10:46.146 --> 10:48.148
Come on.

10:54.238 --> 10:58.200
- He's got Winters! Goddam it!
- Damn it, Sean!

11:08.669 --> 11:11.338
All units, pin 'em in!

11:13.090 --> 11:15.342
Close in on 'em!

11:21.598 --> 11:24.101
One of yours, Sean?

11:26.103 --> 11:27.855
Shit!

11:41.618 --> 11:44.705
Out. Come on. Go, go!

11:47.040 --> 11:48.959
Goddam it, Sean!

12:01.138 --> 12:03.974
Take off now.

12:09.229 --> 12:12.149
- Fly!
- I can't!

12:12.316 --> 12:14.818
Fly, bitch!

12:26.997 --> 12:29.833
All units, locked and ready.
Follow Archer's lead.

12:39.760 --> 12:41.762
What the fuck are you doing?

12:41.845 --> 12:45.015
There's an engine out.
We gotta stop.

13:31.478 --> 13:33.480
- Move, move, move!
- Get back! Back up!

14:05.929 --> 14:08.432
Pollux!

14:11.768 --> 14:13.687
- Cas!
- Get over here.

14:15.606 --> 14:17.608
Back him to me.
Back him to me. He's mine!

14:29.786 --> 14:32.039
Cas.

14:36.043 --> 14:37.961
Secure the hangar.

15:03.987 --> 15:06.073
Berkley, down!

15:20.254 --> 15:23.006
Down!

16:06.717 --> 16:09.052
Give up, Castor. Your time's up.

16:11.388 --> 16:14.725
Well, you better hit me, Sean,
'cause you only got one bullet left.

16:14.892 --> 16:17.561
So do you.

16:17.644 --> 16:22.316
Wow. We've got
something in common.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.735
We both know our guns.

16:24.902 --> 16:29.656
What we don't have in common is that
I don't care if I live, and you do.

16:29.823 --> 16:33.660
Sean, that hurts.

16:33.827 --> 16:36.330
You're not having
any fun, are you, Sean?

16:36.497 --> 16:39.166
Why don't you come with us?
Try terrorism for hire?

16:39.333 --> 16:41.835
- We'll blow some shit up.
It's more fun.
- Shut the fuck up.

16:42.002 --> 16:44.588
You watch your fuckin' mouth!

16:44.755 --> 16:48.926
I'm about to unleash
the biblical plague "Hell-A" deserves,

16:49.092 --> 16:51.595
but I'll give this shithole
a break if my brother and I walk.

16:51.762 --> 16:56.016
- Bullshit.
- Oh-Oh no, I-I see, I see.
Y-You think I'm bluffing.

16:56.099 --> 16:59.520
Maybe I am.
But, then, maybe I'm not.

16:59.686 --> 17:01.939
More importantly, what would
you do with me locked up?

17:02.105 --> 17:04.358
You'd drive your wife
and kid crazy.

17:04.441 --> 17:06.527
Say, how is your daughter,
anyway? Is she ripening by now?

17:06.693 --> 17:09.195
Your... Your darling Janie,
your little peach?

17:09.363 --> 17:12.031
Is she ripe?

17:14.785 --> 17:16.619
Okay.

17:16.787 --> 17:19.039
O-Okay.

17:19.205 --> 17:21.375
Policeman, don't shoot me.

17:23.544 --> 17:26.296
I'm scared, Seanie!

17:29.299 --> 17:31.468
Well, I think you better pull
the trigger,

17:31.635 --> 17:33.554
because I don't give a fuck!

17:33.637 --> 17:35.973
I'm ready

17:36.139 --> 17:39.893
Ready for the big ride, baby

18:08.338 --> 18:12.259
Well, Sean, looks like
Elvis done left the buildin'.

18:24.688 --> 18:28.692
It wasn't my fault.
Why won't you ever be on my side?

18:28.859 --> 18:32.029
I am always on your side,
but you have to give me a chance...

18:32.237 --> 18:34.448
Now what?

18:34.615 --> 18:37.618
She was suspended again. Some kid
made a crack about her clothes...

18:37.743 --> 18:40.704
- She started a fight.
- That's right, Dad.
Don't even ask me what happened.

18:40.871 --> 18:43.540
Okay. What happened?

18:49.213 --> 18:53.467
- Ah, I see.
- Not like you would believe me anyway.

18:53.550 --> 18:56.136
Jamie, look,
it-it-it's not easy, okay?

18:56.303 --> 19:00.474
I mean, loo... You change the way
you look every week.

19:00.557 --> 19:05.103
And-And the way you act.
Who are you supposed to be now?

19:05.229 --> 19:07.481
I'm supposed to be me.

19:07.689 --> 19:11.109
Not like you have a clue
who I am anyway.

19:18.909 --> 19:21.411
I have to work tonight.

19:21.578 --> 19:25.415
I called to tell you,
but I was on hold for ten minutes,
and I couldn't wait any longer.

19:25.582 --> 19:28.669
I got him, Eve.

19:31.421 --> 19:33.966
It's over.

19:34.091 --> 19:36.051
It's over.

19:38.637 --> 19:40.556
Oh, Sean.

19:43.851 --> 19:47.229
I'll make it up to you
and Jamie. I promise.

19:47.437 --> 19:51.608
I'll put in for a desk job...
Well, I'll... I'll do counselling,
sit down, talk about Mike...

19:51.775 --> 19:53.861
I'll do it, anything you want.

19:55.279 --> 19:57.656
I just want you.

19:57.781 --> 20:00.534
Well, good, 'cause that's
what you're gonna get.

20:00.701 --> 20:02.536
You happy?

20:02.703 --> 20:04.872
Yes. Yeah.

20:34.067 --> 20:36.236
What is all this?

20:37.654 --> 20:41.325
Sir, the CIA sent this over.

20:41.450 --> 20:44.578
I didn't know they catered.
Send it back.

20:44.661 --> 20:46.914
No, wait.

20:48.665 --> 20:51.335
How about, uh...

20:51.376 --> 20:54.171
What about to Anderson,
Montgomery,

20:54.338 --> 20:56.423
Berkley,

20:58.592 --> 21:02.763
Pincus, Gianelli, Winters...

21:41.885 --> 21:43.846
How's Loomis?

21:43.971 --> 21:47.641
Uh, he's gonna need
a little surgery, but, uh,

21:47.808 --> 21:50.644
he'll be okay.

21:50.727 --> 21:53.772
- What's up?
- Special ops. They want a word.

21:53.897 --> 21:55.983
Aw, forget it.
I don't have the time.

21:56.149 --> 21:59.069
Better make time, Sean.

21:59.236 --> 22:01.488
Recovered from the jet wreckage.

22:01.572 --> 22:03.657
Found in Pollux Troy's
briefcase.

22:22.009 --> 22:24.178
Porcelain casing.

22:24.344 --> 22:26.180
Thermal cloak.

22:26.346 --> 22:29.349
Nerve gas
and biological payload.

22:29.474 --> 22:31.602
It's enough to flatten
a square mile.

22:31.810 --> 22:34.354
Then depending on
the prevailing winds,

22:34.438 --> 22:39.443
the fallout'll be a tad worse
than Gulf War syndrome.

22:41.195 --> 22:44.072
A biblical...
A biblical plague to LA.

22:45.699 --> 22:48.368
Where is he?
Where is Pollux Troy?

22:52.581 --> 22:55.959
Why draw the schematic if you're
not gonna build the bomb?

22:56.126 --> 22:58.962
What, is it now a crime
in this country to exercise the mind?

22:59.129 --> 23:03.217
- I'm interested in bomb...
- I won't say another word
until I see my brother.

23:05.052 --> 23:07.471
Any progress?

23:07.638 --> 23:10.307
- I need about ten minutes alone
with this guy.
- Ah, give it a rest.

23:10.474 --> 23:12.726
You got Castor. Just go home.

23:12.893 --> 23:15.145
Look, we're not gonna evacuate
the city on your hunch.

23:15.312 --> 23:18.315
Look, I know Castor too well
for this to be a hunch.

23:18.482 --> 23:23.403
You know what, just-just run
the goddam bureau any way you like.

23:32.162 --> 23:36.250
I could put an agent in his cell.
Maybe Pollux will let it slip.

23:36.416 --> 23:40.087
Oh, come on.
He's a paranoid sociopath.

23:40.254 --> 23:43.674
The only person he'd talk to about
that bomb is his brother, and he's dead.

23:45.175 --> 23:47.761
There is one other possibility.

24:13.287 --> 24:16.707
Oh, God.
You're keeping him alive.

24:16.874 --> 24:20.043
Relax, Archer. He's a turnip.

24:22.713 --> 24:24.715
Oh.

24:24.882 --> 24:28.135
What if you could walk
into Erewhon Prison...

24:28.302 --> 24:32.556
and give Pollux a nice, big
brotherly hug as Castor Troy?

24:34.224 --> 24:36.476
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

24:36.643 --> 24:39.980
Let me try. Malcolm Walsh.

24:40.063 --> 24:42.649
- I run the bio-cover unit
for special ops.
- I know who you are.

24:42.816 --> 24:45.235
- But you don't know what I can do.
- Uh...

24:45.402 --> 24:48.322
Physical alteration.
Augmentation.

24:48.405 --> 24:52.576
Dr Walsh can alter the likeness,
even the voice of a government witness.

24:52.743 --> 24:55.662
I think you'll recognize
this patient.

24:59.166 --> 25:02.669
We had to build your friend Loomis
a whole new ear from scratch.

25:11.762 --> 25:15.516
What we're suggesting for you, Archer,
isn't a permanent transplant like that,

25:15.682 --> 25:18.602
just a temporary trade.

25:18.769 --> 25:20.604
Come here.

25:23.273 --> 25:27.277
With the new anti-inflammatories,
healing takes days, not weeks.

25:27.444 --> 25:29.613
Your blood types won't match,
but Pollux won't know that.

25:29.780 --> 25:32.616
Height difference is negligible.

25:34.368 --> 25:39.206
Skin pigment, eye pigment:
Both almost identical.

25:39.289 --> 25:44.628
We'll use laser shears for the hairline,
microplugs for body hair.

25:44.795 --> 25:49.633
We'll do an abdominoplasti...
take care of those, uh, love handles.

25:49.800 --> 25:53.637
But all that's the easy part.
Here's the real science.

25:53.804 --> 25:57.224
This is a state-of-the-art,
morphogenetic template.

25:57.307 --> 26:00.477
The inside is modeled
on your skull,

26:00.644 --> 26:03.063
the outside exactly like Troy's.

26:03.146 --> 26:07.067
Then we fit his face on top.
Not a replica, but the real thing.

26:07.150 --> 26:09.903
Then we simply connect the muscles,
tear ducts and nerve endings.

26:10.070 --> 26:13.073
- So, you wanna take his face and mine...
- Borrow.

26:13.157 --> 26:15.659
The procedure's
completely reversible.

26:15.826 --> 26:18.579
Y-You think that I want
to do this?

26:18.745 --> 26:20.914
- No. No.
- There's no one else, Sean.

26:20.998 --> 26:24.418
- No!
- You have lived and breathed
Castor Troy for years.

26:24.585 --> 26:26.587
I'll get his gang to talk.
That's what I do.

26:26.753 --> 26:31.758
What if you can't? The bomb will blow,
and Castor Troy will win.

26:35.012 --> 26:38.265
Get out. Go ahead.
Wipe your ass.

26:38.432 --> 26:40.350
Damn, what the hell is
that smell?

26:40.517 --> 26:44.271
He shit in his pants.
Where's Dietrich?

26:44.354 --> 26:49.276
Hello, Sasha. When was the last
time you saw Castor Troy?

26:49.359 --> 26:51.612
- Who cares? He's dead.
- Answer the question.

26:51.778 --> 26:54.281
I know my rights. I don't have
to answer shit.

26:54.448 --> 26:56.366
You're right, but know this:

26:56.533 --> 26:59.953
You're a convicted felon on probation
for harbouring Castor Troy.

27:00.120 --> 27:03.624
One phone call from me, and your son
will end up in a foster home.

27:08.212 --> 27:12.049
I understand why
you would use such a threat.

27:12.216 --> 27:14.885
But you try to take him away
from me, I swear to you...

27:20.140 --> 27:23.393
I haven't seen him for years.

27:37.741 --> 27:40.911
This reeks of you. It's got
your signature all over it.

27:43.413 --> 27:47.835
Maybe, but you ain't got nothin'
on me and you know it.

27:48.001 --> 27:52.005
Maybe so, but I can keep you
within city limits,

27:52.172 --> 27:54.174
or I can talk
to your sister again.

27:54.341 --> 27:57.094
She's right outside.

27:57.261 --> 27:59.847
Only this time I'll be nice.

28:01.265 --> 28:03.600
Hey, Sean,

28:03.767 --> 28:06.019
how's your dead son?

28:14.194 --> 28:19.366
I don't know any...
Okay, okay, I heard somethin'
about the 18th, but that's all I know.

28:28.458 --> 28:32.129
Great. So we got a date.
Now where the hell's the damn bomb?

28:32.296 --> 28:34.548
Only Pollux Troy'll know that.

28:34.631 --> 28:37.134
It's your call, Sean.

28:37.301 --> 28:41.388
- Does Lazarro know your plan?
- No, this is a black bag operation.

28:41.555 --> 28:46.310
Strictly off the books. You can't tell
Lazarro, and you can't tell your wife.

28:48.979 --> 28:50.981
Oh, God.

28:51.148 --> 28:54.735
What are you asking me to do?
Okay, let's see.

28:54.902 --> 28:58.489
You're asking me to...
to break the law,

28:58.655 --> 29:01.408
risk my neck.

29:01.492 --> 29:04.578
And you're asking me to put
in the dark all the people...

29:04.745 --> 29:06.830
that love me...

29:06.997 --> 29:08.832
and trust me.

29:18.342 --> 29:20.260
I'll do it.

30:00.884 --> 30:02.970
Sean.

30:04.137 --> 30:05.973
Sorry I woke you.

30:06.139 --> 30:09.643
I'm glad it's you that woke me.

30:09.726 --> 30:12.563
And not a phone call telling me
you won't be coming home.

30:14.147 --> 30:16.984
But that's a fear I can
finally let go of, huh?

30:27.911 --> 30:31.498
Oh, it's all right, Sean.
It's okay.

30:33.584 --> 30:36.003
I keep...

30:36.086 --> 30:39.173
I keep wanting to move this...

30:39.339 --> 30:41.675
over here, you know?

30:41.758 --> 30:45.429
If it had only been an...
an inch to the left,

30:46.597 --> 30:49.016
Mikey'd be alive.

30:49.099 --> 30:53.604
And you wouldn't be.

30:53.770 --> 30:56.857
Sean, things are gonna get
better now that you're home.

30:57.024 --> 31:01.195
The scar won't move,
but it will heal if you let it.

31:01.278 --> 31:05.699
Everything will be better
now that he is forever out of our lives.

31:16.126 --> 31:19.713
Eve, if I told you
that I realize that...

31:19.796 --> 31:22.132
that this thing
won't fully end...

31:24.718 --> 31:27.471
u-until I did one last thing...

31:28.889 --> 31:31.558
Eve, something vital.

31:34.478 --> 31:38.065
Okay... I... You're going
back on assignment again.

31:39.316 --> 31:41.568
This one last time.

31:42.819 --> 31:45.239
Come on, Eve.

31:49.409 --> 31:52.913
"I'm going anywhere,"
that's what you told me.

31:53.080 --> 31:54.915
Oh.

32:00.671 --> 32:04.258
You don't need me to tell you
what to do, Sean. You never have. So go.

32:05.759 --> 32:07.594
But go now.

32:33.954 --> 32:38.375
Sean, I changed my mind.
This is a suicide mission.

32:38.542 --> 32:40.711
Yeah, I know, I know.

32:43.130 --> 32:47.134
You know, maybe this, uh...
this doctor... if he... if he...

32:47.301 --> 32:50.721
If he can do even half
of what he says he can do,

32:50.888 --> 32:53.807
maybe it'll work, I don't know.

32:53.974 --> 32:56.476
I'd become Castor Troy,
be in control.

32:56.643 --> 32:58.979
That's the part that scares me.

33:04.818 --> 33:07.488
Doctor, I have, uh, something...

33:08.655 --> 33:10.741
I have this scar... that... that...

33:10.908 --> 33:15.829
that if you can p-put this back
after, after all this is over...

33:15.913 --> 33:18.165
It... It's important to me.
It's... It's like a reminder.

33:18.332 --> 33:20.751
Sure.

33:25.005 --> 33:29.009
Tito, please,
hold this for me. Please.

33:32.179 --> 33:34.932
Okay. Let's go.

34:45.335 --> 34:47.670
Oh, G...

35:50.400 --> 35:52.319
Oh, my God.

37:03.724 --> 37:06.643
Hey, you okay? Come on.
Talk to me, Sean.

37:16.320 --> 37:19.656
Fuck you! Fuck you! Fuck you!

37:19.865 --> 37:21.950
- Sean! Sean!
- Fuck you!

37:22.075 --> 37:25.829
Sean, come on. Sit down.
Sit down. Sit down.

