01:41:39.099 --> 01:41:42.102
They're concerned
about the constitutionality
of your gestapo tactics!

01:41:42.227 --> 01:41:44.605
And frankly,
so am I! I'm...

01:41:47.024 --> 01:41:49.067
Uh, okay, Victor,

01:41:49.193 --> 01:41:53.030
I'll give the, uh,
taxpayers a break.

01:41:53.155 --> 01:41:55.115
But, um,

01:41:57.409 --> 01:42:00.704
I have something, uh,
I want to confess.

01:42:00.829 --> 01:42:03.999
And I don't think
you're gonna like it.

01:42:04.082 --> 01:42:06.502
I am Castor Troy.

01:42:17.404 --> 01:42:20.407
- Kimmy. Kim?
- Yes, sir.

01:42:20.491 --> 01:42:23.827
Call the paramedics. Victor
Lazarro's had a heart attack.

01:42:23.953 --> 01:42:26.121
- Oh, God. Right away.
- Thank you.

01:42:51.981 --> 01:42:53.899
Home.

01:43:17.423 --> 01:43:19.341
Eve.

01:43:21.760 --> 01:43:23.596
Eve.

01:43:23.679 --> 01:43:26.348
No. Honey, please,
please don't scream.

01:43:26.432 --> 01:43:28.350
Don't scream.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

01:43:28.434 --> 01:43:31.061
Okay, just don't,
don't, don't, don't.

01:43:31.145 --> 01:43:33.272
Just don't...
don't look at my face.

01:43:33.397 --> 01:43:36.567
And the voice.
Don't listen.

01:43:36.650 --> 01:43:39.862
- Just...
- I know who you are!
You killed our son!

01:43:39.987 --> 01:43:42.615
I did not kill our son.

01:43:42.740 --> 01:43:44.617
I'm Sean.

01:43:49.747 --> 01:43:52.583
The last time I saw you...

01:43:52.666 --> 01:43:54.668
was in this room.

01:43:54.793 --> 01:43:58.422
We had a fight when I said
I had to go away again.

01:43:58.505 --> 01:44:01.592
And I spent the night
in Mike's old bed.

01:44:14.772 --> 01:44:17.358
I'm tired, Eve.

01:44:17.483 --> 01:44:22.071
The assignment was to enter
a federal prison as Castor Troy.

01:44:22.196 --> 01:44:25.157
It's just fucking insane.

01:44:25.241 --> 01:44:29.328
And it's... A special ops
surgeon, uh, gave me, uh,

01:44:29.453 --> 01:44:31.455
Castor's face!

01:44:34.208 --> 01:44:37.878
Then, uh... And then, somehow,
Castor came out of his, uh,

01:44:39.672 --> 01:44:44.343
his-his coma, and
he killed everybody...

01:44:44.426 --> 01:44:46.679
who knew about the mission.

01:44:46.804 --> 01:44:50.558
But, but not before
transforming into me.

01:45:12.580 --> 01:45:16.417
I know you don't believe a word
I'm saying. Well, here's proof, Doctor.

01:45:16.542 --> 01:45:20.379
Your husband, me, my,
Sean's blood type is O-negative.

01:45:20.504 --> 01:45:23.215
Castor's is AB.

01:45:32.516 --> 01:45:35.144
And I love you.

01:45:49.116 --> 01:45:51.035
Get some backup.

01:45:55.664 --> 01:45:58.209
What a day.

01:46:01.587 --> 01:46:04.381
You look tense.

01:46:08.761 --> 01:46:13.098
I know I've been acting
different lately. Strange.

01:46:14.600 --> 01:46:18.312
I've got a confession
to make, Eve.

01:46:18.437 --> 01:46:21.440
You're not gonna like it.

01:46:21.524 --> 01:46:24.985
Oh, Eve. I feel...
I feel so close to you.

01:46:26.487 --> 01:46:29.907
I read your diary. I know
I shouldn't have. I'm ashamed.

01:46:29.990 --> 01:46:32.076
But I did.

01:46:32.159 --> 01:46:34.787
I just wanna be the man
that you deserve...

01:46:34.912 --> 01:46:37.498
passionate, tender.

01:46:41.627 --> 01:46:45.381
Victor Lazarro died today.
He had a heart seizure.

01:46:45.506 --> 01:46:48.342
My mentor, gone.

01:46:49.718 --> 01:46:52.179
First Tito, then Victor.
So what?

01:46:54.932 --> 01:46:57.726
I hope this doesn't mean
I'm losing you.

01:46:57.852 --> 01:46:59.728
Of course not.

01:47:07.653 --> 01:47:10.281
You're the only family
I've got.

01:48:00.623 --> 01:48:02.541
Oh, God.

01:48:06.587 --> 01:48:11.175
- Oh, God.
- I was hoping you'd come here.

01:48:11.258 --> 01:48:14.011
Thank you for trusting me.

01:48:16.597 --> 01:48:21.852
Right now,
I don't trust anyone.

01:48:21.936 --> 01:48:25.022
Eve, wh-where'd
you get that gun?

01:48:25.105 --> 01:48:27.316
I took it
from my fake husband.

01:48:27.441 --> 01:48:30.694
Put it down.
You know I'm Sean.

01:48:30.778 --> 01:48:34.448
Do I? Maybe Sean's
already dead, huh?

01:48:34.573 --> 01:48:37.493
I'm moving very slowly.

01:49:00.516 --> 01:49:04.019
I was thinking
the other day, I...

01:49:04.144 --> 01:49:06.021
I remember...

01:49:06.146 --> 01:49:09.275
I once took a date out...

01:49:09.400 --> 01:49:11.485
for surf and turf,

01:49:11.610 --> 01:49:15.573
not knowing she was
a vegetarian.

01:49:15.656 --> 01:49:20.202
So she ate bread.

01:49:20.327 --> 01:49:23.539
And, uh, and broke her tooth
on a rye seed.

01:49:27.126 --> 01:49:30.462
And we, we drove around
all night,

01:49:30.588 --> 01:49:34.592
uh, looking for a...
for a all-night dentist.

01:49:34.675 --> 01:49:38.220
And, and he, uh...
He was so drunk,

01:49:38.345 --> 01:49:40.890
he fixed the wrong tooth.

01:49:46.854 --> 01:49:50.482
And it... When I
finally brought her home...

01:49:53.694 --> 01:49:59.074
Even though it must have
hurt like hell,

01:49:59.200 --> 01:50:02.786
you, you, you kissed me.

01:50:14.590 --> 01:50:18.260
Sean,

01:50:18.385 --> 01:50:22.223
that man...

01:50:22.348 --> 01:50:25.643
You know we've been living
together as man and wife for a week.

01:50:25.726 --> 01:50:28.562
Yeah, I...

01:50:28.687 --> 01:50:33.317
I know.
Eve. Eve.

01:50:33.400 --> 01:50:36.362
I put you
in that position and, and...

01:50:36.445 --> 01:50:39.198
l-l-I can never
make it up to you.

01:50:46.080 --> 01:50:48.749
Well, you're damn well
gonna try.

01:50:48.874 --> 01:50:51.710
Let me take a look at that wound
before you bleed to death.

01:50:59.301 --> 01:51:01.554
With Lazarro out of the way,

01:51:01.679 --> 01:51:04.723
Castor's the new acting director
of the Bureau.

01:51:04.807 --> 01:51:08.060
- He's untouchable.
- Not tomorrow.

01:51:08.185 --> 01:51:10.354
Tomorrow he'll
be at Victor's service.

01:51:10.437 --> 01:51:14.066
Tomorrow.

01:51:14.149 --> 01:51:16.569
That will be the day.

01:51:20.239 --> 01:51:22.825
I want you and Jamie away from
there. Give him a good excuse.

01:51:22.908 --> 01:51:24.827
I can cover for Jamie,

01:51:24.952 --> 01:51:27.079
but if I'm not coming he's
gonna know that something's up.

01:51:28.956 --> 01:51:31.709
And besides, I'm the only one
who can try and explain the truth.

01:51:33.627 --> 01:51:36.672
Excuse me, Mr Archer.
May I help you?

01:51:36.755 --> 01:51:38.924
Dr Levine to X Ray.

01:51:50.895 --> 01:51:53.480
Sean, what are you
doing here?

01:51:58.903 --> 01:52:01.655
Sorry, darling, it...

01:52:01.780 --> 01:52:05.242
I just get so,
so jealous, I...

01:52:05.326 --> 01:52:08.037
I mean, wh-wh-what is a guy
to think when his, uh,

01:52:08.120 --> 01:52:10.039
his wife runs off
in the middle of the night?

01:52:10.122 --> 01:52:13.375
That I'm a doctor that's on call,
so please let me get back to work, okay?

01:52:13.459 --> 01:52:15.377
Sorry.

01:52:18.797 --> 01:52:22.968
Lies, distrust,
mixed messages.

01:52:23.093 --> 01:52:25.012
This is turning
into a real marriage.

01:52:45.658 --> 01:52:49.537
How's Adam?

01:52:49.662 --> 01:52:52.998
I took him over to my cousin's
until this whole thing blows over.

01:52:53.123 --> 01:52:55.626
- Where's Jamie?
- That's what I'd like to know.

01:52:55.709 --> 01:52:58.504
She stole $50 from my purse
and took off.

01:53:00.798 --> 01:53:04.969
- So what's the next move?
- This isn't your fight.

01:53:05.094 --> 01:53:08.639
Oh, come on. You're surprised?
Our daughter won't even
visit Michael's grave.

01:53:08.722 --> 01:53:11.183
You think she gives a damn
about your boss?

01:53:16.856 --> 01:53:20.985
He killed my brother. I'm not
gonna let him take you too.

01:53:35.708 --> 01:53:40.504
Whatever happens,
I promise...

01:53:40.588 --> 01:53:43.299
Sean Archer is
off your back for good.

01:53:57.021 --> 01:54:00.941
My dear friends, we are here
to celebrate the life of Victor Lazarro.

01:55:32.700 --> 01:55:35.286
Somebody back there asked me
to give this to you.

01:55:57.516 --> 01:56:00.144
In peace now, let us take
our brother Victor...

01:56:00.269 --> 01:56:02.354
to his place of rest.

01:56:49.026 --> 01:56:51.070
Isn't this religious?

01:56:54.240 --> 01:56:58.911
Ah, yes. The eternal battle
between good and evil,

01:56:59.036 --> 01:57:00.913
saint and sinner.

01:57:01.038 --> 01:57:03.499
But you're still
not having any fun!

01:57:13.092 --> 01:57:15.135
Honey? Honey?

01:57:17.680 --> 01:57:19.807
Come here.

01:57:22.893 --> 01:57:27.064
And guess what.
Your daughter's on the way.

01:57:27.147 --> 01:57:29.650
History repeats itself.

01:57:35.614 --> 01:57:39.243
This is between us.
Leave them out of it.

01:57:39.368 --> 01:57:43.998
No, you should've
left them out of it.

01:57:44.123 --> 01:57:47.626
Your son was an accident.
I wanted to kill you.

01:57:50.421 --> 01:57:53.549
But you took it
so personally.

01:57:53.632 --> 01:57:57.219
Why didn't you just
kill yourself or let it go?

01:57:57.303 --> 01:58:00.389
- No father could.
- No brother could either.

01:58:00.472 --> 01:58:03.475
Neither could a sister.

01:58:03.601 --> 01:58:05.603
Hey, baby.

01:58:08.981 --> 01:58:11.942
Sasha, what the fuck
are you doing here?

01:58:12.067 --> 01:58:14.069
Gee, Archer, I guess
I'm crashing.

01:58:14.153 --> 01:58:18.741
- You okay, baby?
- Yeah. Thanks.

01:58:18.824 --> 01:58:20.951
Sasha, baby.

01:58:21.076 --> 01:58:23.704
I'm Castor.
That's Archer.

01:58:23.829 --> 01:58:26.749
And I'm bored.

01:58:26.832 --> 01:58:30.544
- Put the fucking gun down.
- Why don't you put your guns down?

01:58:37.510 --> 01:58:39.929
What a predicament!

01:59:38.153 --> 01:59:40.489
Take care of our boy.

01:59:41.740 --> 01:59:44.201
You love him so much.

01:59:44.326 --> 01:59:47.663
Don't let him grow up
to be like us, promise?

01:59:49.915 --> 01:59:51.876
- Yeah.
- Say yeah.

02:00:21.488 --> 02:00:23.073
Mom?

02:00:42.092 --> 02:00:43.886
Jamie!

02:00:49.266 --> 02:00:52.019
Jamie, don't!

02:00:58.859 --> 02:01:01.195
Hello, Wanda?
Wanda, this is Eve Archer.

02:01:08.494 --> 02:01:10.246
I have something
crazy to tell you.

02:01:22.758 --> 02:01:26.387
It's a capital crime to try to kill
the next big boss of the FBI, yes?

02:01:26.470 --> 02:01:28.556
- Yes.
- Ah, yes.

02:01:28.639 --> 02:01:30.766
- The penalty...
- What?

02:01:30.891 --> 02:01:32.935
The penalty is death!

02:01:44.238 --> 02:01:46.448
Die. Please, God, die.

02:01:46.532 --> 02:01:48.909
Hold it!

02:01:48.993 --> 02:01:51.203
Good girl, Jamie!
Shoot him!

02:01:51.328 --> 02:01:54.874
Honey, don't listen to him,
honey! He's not your father!
Hear my voice. I'm your father!

02:01:56.375 --> 02:01:58.127
Use your eyes, Jamie.
Shoot him!

02:01:58.252 --> 02:01:59.962
Don't listen to him!
Don't shoot! Just, just...

02:02:00.087 --> 02:02:04.008
This scumbag... This scumbag shot
your brother, Jamie! Kill him!

02:02:07.178 --> 02:02:09.346
Clod.

02:02:09.471 --> 02:02:13.475
No daughter of mine
would shoot so wide.

02:02:13.559 --> 02:02:17.605
Dad, put the gun down.
Put it down.

02:02:19.315 --> 02:02:21.859
Dad, put it down.

02:02:21.984 --> 02:02:26.363
Now we're gonna find out
what's in Papa's bag. Peaches.

02:02:31.577 --> 02:02:33.662
Say goodbye to Papa.

02:02:35.915 --> 02:02:37.583
Jamie!

02:02:44.548 --> 02:02:48.511
Jamie! Jamie! Jamie,
are you all right? Oh, my God.

02:02:49.720 --> 02:02:51.472
Sir, are you okay?

02:03:00.856 --> 02:03:03.984
Please, someone please tell me
what planet I'm on?

02:03:18.958 --> 02:03:21.085
Get down!

02:04:35.201 --> 02:04:36.827
Stop! This is the police!

02:04:36.952 --> 02:04:40.206
Stop immediately or we'll
be forced to open fire!

02:04:41.207 --> 02:04:43.709
Fire! Fire!

02:09:11.227 --> 02:09:14.647
You're right, Sean.
I've misbehaved.

02:09:14.730 --> 02:09:16.482
I need to be punished.

02:09:21.862 --> 02:09:24.448
But remember,
every time...

02:09:24.573 --> 02:09:27.993
you look in the mirror,
you'll see my face.

02:09:45.094 --> 02:09:47.388
Die!

02:10:05.739 --> 02:10:08.450
Ready

02:10:08.576 --> 02:10:12.162
Ready for the big ride

02:10:12.288 --> 02:10:14.915
Baby

02:10:19.169 --> 02:10:21.755
Off of Pico in the middle
of the street.

02:10:29.180 --> 02:10:31.223
You okay, Archer?

02:10:35.436 --> 02:10:38.731
- What did you call me?
- He called you Archer, sir.

02:10:52.828 --> 02:10:58.000
Sean, they're bringing in
their top surgical team from DC.
You're going to be okay.

02:11:45.047 --> 02:11:47.716
When you wake up,
everything will be restored...

02:11:47.842 --> 02:11:50.511
just the way it was.

02:11:52.221 --> 02:11:57.601
My scar.
The one near my heart.

02:11:57.726 --> 02:12:00.521
This old bullet wound.

02:12:00.646 --> 02:12:03.065
- I won't need it any more.
- Okay.

02:13:01.373 --> 02:13:04.543
Dad?

02:13:16.597 --> 02:13:19.308
Dad?

02:13:19.433 --> 02:13:22.895
I'm sorry I shot you.

02:13:31.153 --> 02:13:34.573
I've got something
I have to ask both of you.

02:13:45.251 --> 02:13:47.962
This is, um, Adam.

02:13:48.087 --> 02:13:52.132
And he needs
a place to live.

02:13:52.258 --> 02:13:57.054
Hi. My name's Jamie.

02:13:57.179 --> 02:14:00.975
I'm Adam.

02:14:01.058 --> 02:14:03.435
Why don't you show Adam
his new room?

02:14:03.519 --> 02:14:06.772
Come on.

02:14:06.856 --> 02:14:08.774
Okay.

